cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CR

This paper deals with analyzing personal attacks in online platforms using a combination of crowdsourcing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with analyzing online discourse, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper involves evaluating the performance of a classifier, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
